included.description:
- Led the design effort in bringing the GoToMeeting experience to the browser. Delivered design solutions to ensure communication and collaboration within the browser. Offered cross browser support, mainly on each platform's own WebRTC specification. Worked closely with PMs, engineers, marketing and support team. Increased tNPS by 30% after releasing the onboarding audio setup. 
- Worked with the lead designer on refreshing the 10+ year old GoToMeeting desktop experience. My role includes: creating explorations and innovative solutions to solve customer problems and usability issues, extracting key tasks and user flows from the research data we gathered, communicating across teams on rollout plans, communication plan and onboarding plans, building up interactive prototypes for usability testing and provide design specs to the engineering team.
included.title: Product Designer

included.description:
In this project, we designed a navigation system to give directions to drivers with less distraction, less map reading, and quick and easy destination setup, so you can stop fussing with your GPS and get to your destination.

Activities conducted: brainstorming, user journey, wireframe, prototype and usability testing.
included.title: Seamless Navigation System design

included.description: For this project, our team incorporated Chinese style with the Metro style to create the impression of both "Spring Festival" and "Microsoft" at the same time, by using spaces and blocks for the layout, while implementing bright colors into a red theme that represents the Chinese New Year. The design was sent out all around Seattle and printed for thousands of copies.
included.title: Ticket Design for Microsoft Asian Spring Festival 2013
